  "response": "**The bug:** `crime_00010` — Timezone Roulette at `src/date.ts:29,33`. The literal `\"2026-12-25T07:00:00\"` has no timezone marker, so `new Date(\"…\")` applies the *runtime's* local zone. In CI (UTC) it parses as 07:00 UTC. On a European host (e.g. CET, UTC+1) it parses as 07:00 local = 06:00 UTC — one hour earlier, which flips the \"is the promo open?\" check across midnight UTC and opens the window a day early.\n\n**Responsible literal:** `\"2026-12-25T07:00:00\"` at `src/date.ts:29` (and the date-only `\"2026-12-20\"` at line 33 has the same class of bug).\n\n**Smallest fix:** append `Z` to pin the literal to UTC — matching the CI server's behaviour:\n\n```diff\n- new Date(\"2026-12-25T07:00:00\")\n+ new Date(\"2026-12-25T07:00:00Z\")\n```\n\nThat's a one-character change, no rename, no signature change, and production now parses the promo start at the same instant CI does.",
